#X text 557 65 Here's a similar example. We have a stereo patch based on [superosc~] (a wave stacking oscillator \, where we stack 5 of them)! The stereo is taken care via multichannel connections. As a variation \, we also have the [moog~] filter instead. Note that [moog~] has a buil-in overdrive feature \, but it's not like having a module on the input as this is taken care inside a feedback loop inside the filter. It does relate to the same idea nonetheless. For last \, we're retriggering the LFO at every new note., f 70;
